  "body": "Followup of https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/pull/15110 cc @ulisesmac \r\n\r\n\"I'm new to Status\" screen is not adjusted to small device screens, as a result content (buttons) can be partially cut. \r\n\r\nBug has been faced by @qoqobolo on her iPhone SE (video below), but can be reproduced by emulating devices with relatively small screens. \r\n\r\nSteps: \r\n\r\n1. Install Status app\r\n2. Go to \"I'm new to Status\" screen\r\n3. See if the whole content is visible on devices with small screens\r\n\r\n**Actual result:** \"I'm new to Status\" screen is not adjusted to small device screens, as a result content is partially cut. \r\n\r\n**Real device iPhone SE (Size: 4.7, resolution: 1334*750)**\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97245802/224971108-fc29e250-6341-4a9b-bf26-363c89977bcf.MP4\r\n\r\n**Emulated Nexus One (Size: 3.7, resolution: 480*800 )**\r\n\r\n<img width=\"477\" alt=\"Android Emulator - Nexus_One_API_32:5554 2023-03-14 12-19-32\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/97245802/224970245-368411ed-c1b1-4fc2-9725-54f204903b61.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
